full_threads.body:
Hi Heath,

I've just come off a call with Joel and Charlie regarding transition. A point that I raised was the web site contact form. As I'm still trading stock in the USA, I will need the current contact form to remain with perhaps a small change to reflect the warehouse details in the USA. Importantly, it will still need to point to enquiry@spidertarp.com . Australian enquiries will need another contact form/address pointing to the Mayo Hardware team, perhaps enquiry@spidertarp.com.au. If there is a delay in the transfer of the he domain spidertarp.com.au I can always manually forward Australian enquiries to the Mayo Hardware POC.

Appreciate your thoughts.

Cheers,

Graeme

Graeme BreenManaging Director | Spider Tarp

Hi Team, 

Chris here jumping in on behalf of Heath. 

I think I found the reason for the emails bouncing. It appears there were two misspelled versions of Heath's email used: heath@wolffiq.com.au and heath@wolfiq.con.au. The correct email is heath@wolfiq.com.au

@Graeme, to get started on the migration of the Spider Tarp website please complete the form found here: https://wolfiq.com.au/care-plan-migration/

@Simon, I'll be in touch in a separate thread to confirm your website care plan etc. 

I am also available on 0421 859 547 if there are any questions.
